<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf1c3212-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10270"><num value="10270">§ 10270.</num><heading> Termination of Board</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Board shall cease to exist not later than 1 year after the date on which the Secretary begins disposal of high-level radioactive waste or spent nuclear fuel in a repository.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf1c3213-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/425/tV/s510">Pub. L. 97–425, title V, § 510</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/202/s101/d/tIII">Pub. L. 100–202, § 101(d) [title III]</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1329-104">101 Stat. 1329–104</ref>, 1329–121; <ref href="/us/pl/100/203/tV/s5051">Pub. L. 100–203, title V, § 5051</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1330-251">101 Stat. 1330–251</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
